him and tried to drown him herself.

00:17:03.500 --> 00:17:05.260
Could be!

00:17:05.260 --> 00:17:08.970
Or maybe she bought a Stella
from the school with a lot of money?

00:17:09.230 --> 00:17:12.680
Oh, but she doesn't seem
to be that rich, though?

00:17:12.820 --> 00:17:14.200
Shock...

00:17:15.390 --> 00:17:17.300
Oh, don't mind them.

00:17:17.300 --> 00:17:18.930
They're just jealous.

00:17:19.790 --> 00:17:23.260
You think so too, right, Damian?

00:17:23.260 --> 00:17:25.320
She must be cheating, right?

00:17:25.950 --> 00:17:27.520
Do you really think our school

00:17:27.520 --> 00:17:31.600
is just a third-rate school that'd randomly
give a Stella for a sum of money...

00:17:31.930 --> 00:17:33.520
...or something?

00:17:34.620 --> 00:17:35.700
Well...

00:17:36.490 --> 00:17:38.240
If you're not happy with this school,

00:17:38.240 --> 00:17:40.830
then why don't you
just transfer to another school?

00:17:41.060 --> 00:17:44.100
He's so mature at times like this!

00:17:44.100 --> 00:17:45.840
So cool!

00:17:46.240 --> 00:17:51.580
I'm irritated exactly because
she beat me to it not out of fluke!

00:17:53.370 --> 00:17:56.380
Wow, so he's really a serious guy, huh?

00:17:57.310 --> 00:17:59.600
Come on, class is starting now.

00:18:09.690 --> 00:18:10.610
Anyway,

00:18:10.960 --> 00:18:14.160
have you decided
on your reward yet, Anya?

00:18:14.400 --> 00:18:16.210
I mean, Starlight Anya.

00:18:16.210 --> 00:18:17.120
Reward?

00:18:17.490 --> 00:18:18.610
That's right!

00:18:18.610 --> 00:18:20.690
It's only natural for someone
to get a reward...

00:18:20.690 --> 00:18:23.520
...after they've passed an exam
or won a contest, right?

00:18:23.520 --> 00:18:25.140
I can get peanuts?

00:18:25.140 --> 00:18:27.630
Come on, ask for something
more expensive instead!

00:18:28.080 --> 00:18:33.160
My parents bought me a cute dress
and a tiara for my exams the other day!

00:18:34.450 --> 00:18:35.890
But, well...

00:18:36.070 --> 00:18:38.850
I guess some of the rewards
I got weren't so fancy.

00:18:38.850 --> 00:18:40.140
Huh!

00:18:40.440 --> 00:18:44.900
Is your family a secret organization
that conquers the world?!

00:18:44.900 --> 00:18:47.650
What do you mean?
We're just a normal corporation.

00:18:51.270 --> 00:18:53.210
Then Anya wants a castle!

00:18:53.210 --> 00:18:55.820
I don't think that's within
the realm of possibility here.

00:18:55.820 --> 00:18:57.340
You don't have a place to place it either.

00:18:58.970 --> 00:18:59.660
Then...

00:19:00.090 --> 00:19:02.010
A one-year supply of peanuts?

00:19:02.010 --> 00:19:04.570
That's an easy one, though...

00:19:04.570 --> 00:19:06.220
But are you really okay with that?

00:19:08.230 --> 00:19:10.240
Reward is so confusing...

00:19:10.960 --> 00:19:12.250
Yeah, I guess.

00:19:12.600 --> 00:19:16.580
Well, I guess Wiesel
is the best reward I've ever got.

00:19:16.580 --> 00:19:20.180
Oh, he's my dog.
And what a cute dog he is!

00:19:20.420 --> 00:19:23.680
Wiesel!

00:19:23.950 --> 00:19:25.150
A dog?

00:19:30.310 --> 00:19:32.250
You also have a dog, second son?

00:19:32.250 --> 00:19:32.880
Hm?

00:19:33.470 --> 00:19:34.950
Huh? A dog?

00:19:34.950 --> 00:19:37.200
Why are you asking him?

00:19:39.480 --> 00:19:41.700
Max!

00:19:43.470 --> 00:19:44.700
Who cares?

00:19:45.170 --> 00:19:46.900
Don't talk to me so casually!

00:19:50.290 --> 00:19:52.200
Anya's got a dog too!

00:19:52.200 --> 00:19:55.760
All right! Let's see who's cuter,
my Max or your dog!

00:19:55.760 --> 00:19:58.470
Bring him to my house,
and get your parents too!

00:20:00.210 --> 00:20:02.430
Greetings, Mr. Forger.

00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:05.430
Let's just stop the war, Mr. Desmond.

00:20:05.890 --> 00:20:08.260
The world is now at peace.

00:20:09.850 --> 00:20:10.620
Heh.

00:20:10.620 --> 00:20:11.440
Huh?

00:20:12.270 --> 00:20:13.440
So you want...

00:20:13.970 --> 00:20:15.360
...a dog for your reward?

00:20:15.360 --> 00:20:16.160
Yes.

00:20:16.690 --> 00:20:18.800
Having a pet dog will bring peace.

00:20:18.800 --> 00:20:21.010
Peace? You mean to your heart?

00:20:21.570 --> 00:20:25.580
Hmm... Well, yeah, I've been thinking
of buying you something for a reward, too...

00:20:27.450 --> 00:20:28.460
Anya.

00:20:28.950 --> 00:20:32.530
Having a pet will be tough, you know?

00:20:32.530 --> 00:20:34.680
You must take responsibility for it.

00:20:34.960 --> 00:20:36.260
Responsibility...

00:20:38.920 --> 00:20:40.010
A dog, huh?

00:20:40.640 --> 00:20:41.480
Well...

00:20:42.400 --> 00:20:44.310
Let me consider it for a bit.

00:20:44.310 --> 00:20:45.530
Loid...

00:20:45.530 --> 00:20:46.720
Father...

00:20:46.720 --> 00:20:49.020
If the dog's well-trained,

00:20:49.020 --> 00:20:52.090
it can act as an extra layer
of security for this house.

00:20:53.210 --> 00:20:55.300
Dogs are so ferocious...

00:20:55.300 --> 00:20:59.040
I'm worried if Anya
would be bitten to death by one...

00:21:00.170 --> 00:21:04.590
Anya wants a small and cute dog...

00:21:04.590 --> 00:21:05.200
Huh?

00:21:05.560 --> 00:21:06.930
Oh, yeah, sure.

00:21:10.690 --> 00:21:14.150
Well, I guess there are
some small but clever dogs.

00:21:14.150 --> 00:21:16.560
I'll just have WISE provide one for me.

00:21:17.990 --> 00:21:21.210
All right, let's go visit
the pet shop this weekend.

00:21:26.430 --> 00:21:28.640
So the buyer's decided yet?

00:21:29.510 --> 00:21:32.260
Hmm... They're still reluctant for now.

00:21:32.840 --> 00:21:35.460
They're just some thugs
pretending to be revolutionary...

00:21:36.670 --> 00:21:39.480
What, they're gonna turn it
into a bomb dog or something?

00:21:39.730 --> 00:21:41.980
What poor animals these guys are.

00:21:41.980 --> 00:21:46.030
They've all been tinkered to the bones
to become human's toys.

00:21:51.030 --> 00:21:52.490
Shut your traps, you stupid dogs!

00:21:52.490 --> 00:21:54.500
Keep barking and you'll get no food!

00:21:54.500 --> 00:21:58.940
These dogs don't look like
they got the brains for anything.

00:21:59.790 --> 00:22:02.000
Hey, are Number 3 and
Number 5 getting sicker?

00:22:02.390 --> 00:22:04.510
Like hell I'd care!
Just leave them!

00:22:07.870 --> 00:22:10.220
Man, this place really stinks.

00:22:20.520 --> 00:22:22.030
Anya wants this one...

00:22:22.230 --> 00:22:23.340
Or this one!

00:22:23.340 --> 00:22:25.780
It looks tame and safe.

00:22:32.620 --> 00:22:33.980
Fighting with each other

00:22:33.980 --> 00:22:35.320
'Til almost everything was in ruins

00:22:35.320 --> 00:22:38.820
On this mischievous planet

00:22:38.820 --> 00:22:44.230
I've been an outsider
since the day I was born

00:22:44.230 --> 00:22:48.200
My tears have run dry

00:22:48.200 --> 00:22:54.470
The place I'm going back to is in my dreams

00:22:54.470 --> 00:22:55.840
I met you

00:22:55.840 --> 00:22:57.530
where I came spilling out

00:22:57.530 --> 00:23:00.530
You with all your secrets

00:23:00.530 --> 00:23:05.980
Pretending to be normal

00:23:05.980 --> 00:23:09.990
I'd given up searching
for a place where I belong

00:23:09.990 --> 00:23:17.540
Only to find out I had to
create one for myself all along

00:23:18.330 --> 00:23:20.340
We made a deal that day

00:23:20.950 --> 00:23:23.490
Thicker than blood

00:23:23.490 --> 00:23:28.460
A pact from heart to heart

00:23:28.460 --> 00:23:31.200
Shall we hold hands and head home?

00:23:31.200 --> 00:23:34.020
What should we eat tonight?

00:23:34.020 --> 00:23:36.750
"Here's what happened today"

00:23:36.750 --> 00:23:40.150
That's what I wanted to talk to you about

00:23:40.150 --> 00:23:42.220
Any and every day is

00:23:42.220 --> 00:23:44.790
A comedy with you

00:23:44.790 --> 00:23:47.630
Dancing on a creaking bed

00:23:47.630 --> 00:23:51.710
Rolling around in laughter

00:23:51.710 --> 00:23:58.520
We'll keep on with our
ridiculous everyday life

00:24:06.880 --> 00:24:09.900
(Mission: 12 - Penguin Park)
